                                <div id="GeneralInformation" class="pb60">
                                    <div class="mainHd">Other information For male and female students</div>
                                    <div class="otherInfo justifyContentBetween flexBox">
                                        <div class="inner">
                                            <ul class="countList short">
                                                <li>If the student wants to withdraw from the accommodation, he will
                                                    provide an alternative, provided that it meets the accommodation
                                                    requirements.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>If the substitute student is unable to do so, he is obligated to pay
                                                    the room rent until the end of the year.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>The student will get back the remaining housing fees if he brings an
                                                    alternative.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>Reservations for student housing begin at the end of the academic
                                                    year for old students, and when admission and registration at the
                                                    university opens for new students.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>The housing contract starts on 9/1 and ends on 8/31 (i.e. a full
                                                    year).
                                                </li>
                                                <li>The student is allowed to bring a computer or mobile phone into his
                                                    room, but is prohibited from bringing a television.
                                                </li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="inner">
                                            <ul class="countList short">
                                                <li>Visitors are allowed until 10 pm and non-residents are not allowed
                                                    to stay overnight in the residence without permission.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>The residence gate closes at 11pm, except for those who have an
                                                    emergency, in which case permission must be sought from the
                                                    residence supervisor.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>Current housing is in the apartment system. The apartment contains
                                                    three to four rooms, two to three bathrooms, and a shared kitchen
                                                    for the apartment.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>Available seats in the residences (single rooms - double rooms -
                                                    triple rooms).
                                                </li>
                                                <li>The fees include (rent - electricity and water - maintenance -
                                                    internet - and a security deposit of 5,000 Yemeni riyals, which will
                                                    be returned to the student at the end of the year if the furniture
                                                    provided to him is in good condition).
                                                </li>
